definitions.definition: To complain loudly, to give voice to one's censure or criticism
definitions.label_groups: intransitive , with against or occasionally about , formerly also with on , at , upon

definitions.definition: To draw in or away; to entice , inveigle .

main_definition: ( intransitive , with against or occasionally about , formerly also with on , at , upon ) To complain loudly, to give voice to one's censure or criticism [from 16th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( obsolete , transitive ) To draw in or away; to entice , inveigle . [17th–19th c.]
